long_description: there's more to photography as an art than the technical aspects. anyone can shoot conventional portraits if they have the gear. from my decades of experience in sketching and fine art, it's less about the "proper" lighting, and more about using creative lighting to convey the mood or feeling. my aim is to step beyond the technical, and step into the creative....to step outside the lines, because that is where creativity happens. i want to push beyond the ordinary, and capture what lies inside, because ordinary doesn't stand out from the crowd. with nearly 20 years of fine art experience, i have learned to control the use of lighting to create mood and shape, as well as colour use for capturing personality.
